{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17655417","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17655417"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:01:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:01:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18660"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18660","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18660"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.09,0.69,0.06,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11392"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113962"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11392","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11392"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18660"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95977"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7245"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26405"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26688"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/113962"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior view of the skull reveals several important bones that contribute to facial structure and protect underlying organs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following bones forms the superior orbital margin and contains the frontal sinuses?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Zygomatic bone","Maxillary bone","Frontal bone","Sphenoid bone","Ethmoid bone"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efrontal bone\u003C/strong\u003E forms the forehead region and superior portion of the orbit. It contains the paired frontal sinuses and contributes to the anterior cranial fossa internally. The bone articulates with the nasal bones inferiorly and the parietal bones posteriorly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezygomatic bone\u003C/strong\u003E forms the lateral orbital margin and prominent cheekbone. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emaxillary bone\u003C/strong\u003E forms the inferior orbital margin and floor, upper jaw, and contains the maxillary sinus. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenoid bone\u003C/strong\u003E contributes to the posterior orbit but not the superior orbital margin, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Eethmoid bone\u003C/strong\u003E forms part of the medial orbital wall and contains the ethmoidal air cells, but does not form the superior orbital margin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe frontal bone provides protection to the frontal lobes of the brain while supporting facial structure and housing the frontal sinuses.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The frontal bone forms the forehead and anterior portion of the skull roof.","The frontal bone contains paired frontal sinuses and forms the superior orbital margin.","The frontal bone articulates with the nasal bones inferiorly and the parietal bones posteriorly."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u0022Frontal bone anterior\u0022 by Anatomography is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 2.1jp Unported license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.1/jp/deed.en). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Frontal_bone_anterior.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95977"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18660"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"expla